#3168 So I brought this girl to fraternity's formal and used the venue as a chance to get to know her better. We were friends before, but never close. I'm at the point where I don't know if I want to date her. Not because I wouldn't date her, but because I don't know if I want a relationship. The existential crisis going on in my head lately has been interesting.

#3161 I was looking over someone's shoulder in lecture, and their Facebook was open to MIT Confessions with admin access...Mind = Blown. My life at MIT is complete. xoxo - Your secret is safe with me. ;)

#3158 We are the under-rested--
the overstressed
Backs hunched, fingers rattling keys--
pushing.

We are the "prove myself"s--
the "am I good enough"s
who by some small stroke of luck are bound
by an institution.

Bound by late nights,
by too much caffine,
by self-doubt,
and by relief.

We fought to get here--
We fought to stay here--
We fought to leave here--

We will fight because we have been here.

For today,
For tomorrow--
IHTFP
